01:12:41,180 --> 01:12:45,180
He was here for two days.
He found me himself.

500
01:12:45,380 --> 01:12:49,579
I kicked him out.
I'm telling you the truth.

501
01:12:54,500 --> 01:12:57,779
If you like your honey sweet,
you should like the bees indeed.

502
01:13:00,899 --> 01:13:07,380
Let me go, creeps!
Don't touch me, scum!

503
01:13:07,699 --> 01:13:09,380
Let me go!

504
01:13:10,180 --> 01:13:12,579
Ouch! I'll kill you, bitch!

505
01:13:12,779 --> 01:13:15,779
- Scum!
- Lie down!

506
01:14:42,699 --> 01:14:44,300
I'll kill the motherfucker!

507
01:14:50,699 --> 01:14:56,579
Your people stopped by.
They asked for you.

508
01:14:59,699 --> 01:15:02,579
I really don't know
who you are and where you live.

509
01:15:04,500 --> 01:15:06,380
They didn't believe me.

510
01:15:19,699 --> 01:15:23,180
Their chief had a round mug,

511
01:15:24,500 --> 01:15:26,579
talked in proverbs.

512
01:15:29,180 --> 01:15:30,779
Shall we sing a song?

513
01:15:34,100 --> 01:15:35,979
I'm tone deaf.

514
01:15:38,100 --> 01:15:40,180
Yeah, I understand.

515
01:15:44,699 --> 01:15:48,300
You say he served at HQ?
As a clerk?

516
01:15:49,979 --> 01:15:53,899
First Pinecone, then two more
disappeared.

517
01:15:55,500 --> 01:15:58,979
And now the Mole.
Simple like that.

518
01:16:10,100 --> 01:16:13,579
You live, you learn,
you live and learn.

519
01:16:15,779 --> 01:16:21,779
Yeah. Danny, is that you?
What happened?

520
01:16:23,300 --> 01:16:26,579
Something happened, brother.
You alone?

521
01:16:29,100 --> 01:16:31,380
Good. I'll be there soon
and tell you everything.

522
01:16:43,100 --> 01:16:44,579
He's coming.

523
01:16:59,779 --> 01:17:02,779
-What do you want?
- Gramps, sell me your rifle.

524
01:17:03,380 --> 01:17:05,979
-A million.
- Bring it out.

525
01:17:06,500 --> 01:17:08,579
Give me the money first.

526
01:17:14,100 --> 01:17:16,979
- Dollars!
- There's a million two hundred here.

527
01:17:17,180 --> 01:17:19,579
Drag out all the shells.

528
01:17:34,500 --> 01:17:36,779
Five caliber. For ducks.

529
01:20:41,180 --> 01:20:43,579
You lie here quiet, I'll let you go.

530
01:21:03,300 --> 01:21:05,100
All right. I got it.

531
01:21:08,979 --> 01:21:13,180
Guns on the floor! Hands behind your
heads! Lie down, mugs on the floor!

532
01:21:47,779 --> 01:21:49,180
Viktor, get up.

533
01:21:49,500 --> 01:21:52,579
Don't shoot, brother. Please.

534
01:21:52,779 --> 01:21:55,180
What you saying, brother? Come on,
get up, it's over.

535
01:21:55,699 --> 01:22:00,579
Forgive me, brother.
Don't shoot, please. Don't kill me.

536
01:22:00,779 --> 01:22:05,579
Brother. You're my brother.
You were like a father to me.

537
01:22:07,699 --> 01:22:11,380
I even called you papa.

538
01:22:13,699 --> 01:22:15,979
You remember how I cut my leg
when we went fishing?

539
01:22:16,180 --> 01:22:18,579
You dragged me home,
ten kilometers.

540
01:22:21,100 --> 01:22:26,180
Remember how I got scared of a cat-
fish? And you just laughed at me?

541
01:22:31,380 --> 01:22:32,699
You promised.

542
01:22:34,899 --> 01:22:37,380
I keep my word.

543
01:22:39,380 --> 01:22:42,579
And you tell your people: I'll whack
whoever touches my brother.

544
01:22:43,699 --> 01:22:44,979
Go.

545
01:22:46,180 --> 01:22:50,579
- It was him who betrayed you.
- I know.

546
01:22:50,779 --> 01:22:53,579
- Forgive me, brother.
- Cut it out.

547
01:22:54,699 --> 01:22:56,579
Where's the money?

548
01:22:58,380 --> 01:23:02,100
In his briefcase.
He took everything, the creep.

549
01:23:15,100 --> 01:23:17,579
You go home. To mama.

550
01:23:18,899 --> 01:23:23,180
She's getting old.
Needs help.

551
01:23:26,380 --> 01:23:28,300
Give her the money.

552
01:23:30,979 --> 01:23:34,899
Get a job, with the police.

553
01:23:36,380 --> 01:23:39,579
Uncle Kolya is the chief there,

554
01:23:39,779 --> 01:23:41,979
he was dad's classmate.

555
01:23:46,380 --> 01:23:48,300
They've got an opening.

556
01:23:51,899 --> 01:23:53,779
Don't take the train.

557
01:23:55,699 --> 01:23:58,180
Hitchhike out of the city.

558
01:24:10,180 --> 01:24:14,180
Well, brother? So long.

559
01:24:18,699 --> 01:24:20,380
If God wills it, we'll see each other
sometime.

560
01:24:23,300 --> 01:24:25,579
Did you forget, you piece of shit?

561
01:24:25,899 --> 01:24:28,779
You forgot what I told you?

562
01:24:29,699 --> 01:24:33,380
-You forgot?
- Pavel!

563
01:24:33,699 --> 01:24:35,579
I'll break you of your whoring!

564
01:24:41,500 --> 01:24:44,300
I'll make that fancy pants little
retard of yours eat shit!

565
01:24:45,180 --> 01:24:48,180
Where is he?
Where's that asshole? Huh?

566
01:24:48,380 --> 01:24:49,779
Here I am.

567
01:24:51,300 --> 01:24:54,180
Ah! Mr. Cool's arrived.

568
01:24:55,699 --> 01:24:58,180
Well, brother, how we gonna
split the bitch?

569
01:24:58,699 --> 01:25:00,579
You're not my brother.

570
01:25:03,699 --> 01:25:05,180
Pavel!

571
01:25:07,699 --> 01:25:10,899
Take your hands of it!
Hold on, hold on.

572
01:25:12,100 --> 01:25:13,579
It's okay, Pavel, it's okay.

573
01:25:13,779 --> 01:25:16,979
Quiet, quiet.
It's okay, Pavel.

574
01:25:26,180 --> 01:25:27,180
Sveta!

575
01:25:27,779 --> 01:25:30,979
Come on, shoot!
Kill everybody, come on!

576
01:25:31,779 --> 01:25:33,779
You're the big man here!

577
01:25:33,979 --> 01:25:36,899
What's it cost you to kill a man?
You, a clerk!

578
01:25:38,100 --> 01:25:40,100
- Sveta!
- Get out!

579
01:25:40,300 --> 01:25:41,979
Get me a towel.

580
01:25:43,100 --> 01:25:45,579
Sveta, I came foryou.

581
01:25:47,699 --> 01:25:51,180
I got money. Can we leave?

582
01:25:51,500 --> 01:25:54,899
Quiet, Pavel, quiet.
We'll take care of you.

583
01:25:56,699 --> 01:25:59,579
- Sveta!
- I told you to leave.

584
01:26:00,500 --> 01:26:02,579
Don't come here anymore.

585
01:26:03,500 --> 01:26:05,380
I don't love you.

586
01:26:06,500 --> 01:26:09,779
It's okay, Pavel.
Everything's going to be fine.

587
01:26:19,500 --> 01:26:21,899
I brought you an album.

588
01:26:33,180 --> 01:26:39,380
This money... since you got it...
give some... for treatment.

589
01:26:40,180 --> 01:26:42,300
You see how it is...

590
01:28:03,699 --> 01:28:08,180
You said it: the city is a force.
And here everyone's weak.

591
01:28:11,699 --> 01:28:16,579
The city is a dark force. The strong
come here and become weak.

592
01:28:17,699 --> 01:28:19,579
The city takes our strength.

593
01:28:22,779 --> 01:28:24,779
And now you've fallen.

594
01:28:30,779 --> 01:28:32,579
Here, take this.

595
01:28:35,500 --> 01:28:39,180
What's the problem? Take it. There's
a lot here. You'll live for a while.

596
01:28:43,500 --> 01:28:46,380
What's good for the Russian
is death forthe German.

597
01:29:11,300 --> 01:29:14,380
Okay, German, so long.

598
01:29:18,300 --> 01:29:19,779
Thank you.

599
01:29:51,699 --> 01:29:53,579
Guys, have you seen Kat?

600
01:29:53,779 --> 01:29:56,180
Look in McDonalds.

601
01:30:19,699 --> 01:30:23,779
If it's because of the dough, you're
wasting your time. I didn't take it.

602
01:30:26,100 --> 01:30:29,979
-What are you going to do?
- I don't know.

603
01:30:30,699 --> 01:30:34,500
I may go to the Pyramid, or to the
Planetarium, only it's expensive.

604
01:30:35,699 --> 01:30:37,579
Penkin's playing today.

605
01:30:38,300 --> 01:30:40,180
Right now it's too early to think.

606
01:30:43,180 --> 01:30:46,380
Pinocchio, dish out sixty thousand.

607
01:30:46,699 --> 01:30:49,579
We'll each take a hit of acid.
And in the evening I'll treat you.

608
01:30:52,300 --> 01:30:53,979
I'm leaving town.

609
01:30:57,380 --> 01:30:59,300
What did you want then?

610
01:31:01,100 --> 01:31:04,180
- To say goodbye.
-Well, later.

611
01:31:12,699 --> 01:31:15,180
Take it. Go see the Penkin concert.

612
01:31:19,500 --> 01:31:20,979
What's this for?

613
01:31:24,380 --> 01:31:26,300
Is this for me or something?

614
01:31:26,500 --> 01:31:28,500
Okay, later.

615
01:31:30,300 --> 01:31:32,180
Maybe you need something?

616
01:31:34,100 --> 01:31:35,579
Well, I'm outta here?

617
01:32:09,979 --> 01:32:11,899
I haven't sat out my discharge yet.

618
01:32:13,500 --> 01:32:15,380
Where did you serve?

619
01:32:16,500 --> 01:32:20,180
In HQ there, I sat out my hitch
as a clerk, you know...

620
01:32:21,500 --> 01:32:23,380
And what do you want to be?

621
01:32:23,699 --> 01:32:27,579
Me? Don't know.
A driver.

622
01:32:33,899 --> 01:32:35,899
Hey, can I switch on some music?

623
01:32:36,100 --> 01:32:38,100
I haven't listened to it for awhile.

624
01:32:38,300 --> 01:32:39,699
Go ahead.

625
01:33:00,899 --> 01:33:02,779
The snow's really piled up, huh?

626
01:33:06,979 --> 01:33:08,579
Yeah.

627
01:33:12,899 --> 01:33:14,779
Where you headed?

628
01:33:17,300 --> 01:33:19,180
To Moscow.
